The paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) for computer vision tasks, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the role of vector processing hardware in CNN implementations, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and parallel computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes a unified CNN framework for both high-level and low-level vision tasks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
